Scalloped Corn
  -- Laura Kanya

2 large eggs
1 c reduced-fat milk
8 c fresh or thawed frozen corn kernels, divided
4 tbsp unsalted butter, melted, divided
2 scallions, thinly sliced, plus more for garnish
1 tsp salt
1/2 tsp smoked paprika
1/2 tsp onion powder
1/4 tsp ground pepper
1 1/2 c crushed saltine crackers (from 1 cracker sleeve), divided

Preheat oven to 350F. Coat a 9x13" baking dish with cooking spray. Place eggs, milk, 4 c corn and 1 tbsp melted butter in a blender. Process until creamy and smooth, about 1 minute. Transfer to a large bowl; stir in scallions, salt, paprika, onion powder, pepper, 1/2 cup crushed saltines and the remaining 4 cups corn. Pour the mixture into the prepared baking dish. Stir the remaining 3 tbsp melted butter and 1 c crushed saltines together in a small bowl. Sprinkle evenly over the corn mixture. Bake until browned and firm to the touch, ~40 min. Let stand for 5 min. Garnish with additional scallions, if desired.

